Hi guys.

I want to ask all of u about watching .mkv movies in notebook.When I watch a .mkv 
in my notebook , it seems like a divx or slightly better than it.I know the LCD panel 
of it isnt HD but I just wonder that does it really make a huge difference watching it in 
a 42" or 46" LCD or LED TV ?

Thx for ur answers guys.And thx for the movie again.

@TheChosen1_

MKV files are containers, usually for hd films.
If you watch it on a little laptop you wont notice that its HD as your laptop will only display at whatever the maximum res for that laptop is.
When you output to an HD tv or monitor that has a hd screen, you will see a big difference.
If you're only going to watch movies on a little laptop then ur better off downloading small 700mb files.
